                     ProFTPD Mirror Maintenance Scripts
                     ==================================

These scripts check whether mirrors are up-to-date, and generate web pages
and the DNS zone's subfile for the mirror network.

These scripts require Python (2.4+ should be fine), and the Python MySQLdb
and pyme (GPG signature verification via GPGME) modules.

addMirror.php requires a working PHP interpreter and the PHP mysql
extension.

    o addMirror.php (web page)
      Submit a new mirror. This is the script behind
      http://mirrors.proftpd.org/.

    o check-mirrors
      Check all mirrors to ensure they are reachable, up-to-date,
      and whether the PGP and MD5 signatures on the source tarballs
      in distrib/source are valid.

    o dns-zone
      Generate a DNS zone subfile for the mirror network.

    o mirror-list
      Generate a proftpd.org web page for the mirror network. Must be run
      twice, once for each mirror type (www, ftp).

    o update-dns-zone
      Automatically generate a new DNS zone subfile and commit it.

These jobs run on a nightly basis from proftpd@boost.horde.net's crontab.

